@node MAIN "HTML Syntax Parser"

@{fg shine}ENGLISH @{"DEUTSCH" link DEUTSCH}@{fg text}

@{b}CONTENTS@{ub}

  Extended HTML parser for GoldED's Webworld mode with support for
  HTML, PHP, JavaScript, JSP, ASP and HSC.
  Highlighting of Script-Code (Strings, Blocks, Parenthesis, etc.)

@{b}INSTALLATION@{ub}

  To install this parser, run  the  provided  setup  program.  To
  revert  back  to  the original GoldED syntax parser, repeat the
  installation und choose UNINSTALL when prompted.

  1. Doubleclick the setup icon.
  2. Go to the Preferences of GoldED / Webworld and set the new colors.
     You will reach this by the menu "extra" -> "change settings",
     then click on the tab "filetypes", go to the list and open the
     "webworld" node. Then you will find the entry "color codes",
     which can be opened by double-clicking on it.
  3. Choose the colors for the code-highlighting as you prefer it.
  4. Set the file-activation to "#?.(htm|html|php|php3|inc|jsp|asp|hsc)"
     In the webworld node (see 2.) there is a node "file-activation" too,
     which has only one entry; thisone can be changes by clicking two
     times on it - but with a pause inbetween - not a double-click !
  5. Happy programming - have fun !

@endnode
